{"id": "duc04-testb-17:1#4", "contents": "The US Secretary of State, Madeleine Albright, has expressed her expectation that Israel's Cabinet will ratify the new peace accord within the next few days, despite the recent market bombing. In a phone call with Netanyahu, Albright conveyed that the US understands the delay but anticipates the agreement to be approved soon. Meanwhile, the radical group Islamic Jihad has claimed responsibility for the market bombing and vowed to carry out further attacks in an attempt to block the peace accord. The group's leader, Ramadan Abdullah Shallah, confirmed the claim in an interview with Radio Monte Carlo."}
